      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0623P0-03934'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0623P0_20010315_GCR_243' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        <span class="member">Lord Whitty</span> moved Amendment No. 215:
        <q>Page 55, leave out lines 29 to 35.</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0623P0-03935'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0623P0_20010315_GCR_244' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: These are tidying-up amendments. In rising to move Amendment No. 215, I shall speak also to Amendments Nos. 218 and 221. These amendments delete powers that would otherwise be granted under the Bill to specify in regulations the form and content of three notices that are part of the enfranchisement process&#x2014;the notice of invitation to participate, the participation notice and the initial notice to commence the enfranchisement process. There is already a general power under the 1993 Act to make regulations on the form and content of any enfranchisement notice, and the specific powers, which are on the face of the Bill, are unnecessary duplications. I beg to move.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0623P0-03936'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0623P0_20010315_GCR_245' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
